com.pcloud.sdk

Class UploadOptions

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.pcloud.sdk.UploadOptions

  • public final class UploadOptions
extends java.lang.Object
    A container for the possible options when creating file.

    UploadOptions is a immutable container for the allowed options when creating files through ApiClient.createFile(RemoteFolder, String, DataSource, Date, ProgressListener, UploadOptions), ApiClient.createFile(RemoteFolder, String, DataSource, UploadOptions). ApiClient.createFile(long, String, DataSource, Date, ProgressListener, UploadOptions), or ApiClient.createFile(long, String, DataSource, UploadOptions)

    Instances of the class can be created either the create() method or by mutating an existing object by calling newBuilder().

    The DEFAULT instance is pre-configured for the most common usage cases.

    • Field Detail

      • DEFAULT

        public static final UploadOptions DEFAULT
        The default instance of UploadOptions.
        • Files WILL BE NOT overridden on the server but instead saved with a number in the end.
        • Partial uploads (files not fully red before a connection break) WILL NOT BE saved on the server

      • OVERRIDE_FILE

        public static final UploadOptions OVERRIDE_FILE
        The default instance of UploadOptions.
        • Files WILL BE overridden on the server.
        • Partial uploads (files not fully red before a connection break) WILL NOT BE saved on the server

      • PARTIAL_UPLOAD

        public static final UploadOptions PARTIAL_UPLOAD
        The default instance of UploadOptions.
        • Files WILL BE NOT overridden on the server but instead saved with a number in the end.
        • Partial uploads (files not fully red before a connection break) WILL BE saved on the server
